  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: a0bdb16889ee11c44b0783c2bc51a41c, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 30
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 0
    m_MaxSize: 50
    m_Alignment: 1
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 1
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: 'The four realms and old gods: Every realm possesses a ruling figure conjured
    at the beginning of time, the only exception being the mortal realm.  Abraham
    is the ruler of heaven, Aletheia is the ruler of purgatory, and Lucifer is the
    ruler of hell.  These gods watch over the mortal realm delegating the souls to
    whatever realm they fit in based on their virtues and sins.  Because of their
    limitless power, they have made a pact to never interfere with events that take
    place in the mortal realm, as a mortal mind would collapse at the sight of such
    power.  Despite this, Aletheia was the only god to vote against this pact and
    because of this, she remains untrustworthy in the eyes of Abraham and Lucifer. 
    They wait for the day when the right specimen will come along and put an end
    to the purgatorial god and restore order.'
