      m_Calls: []
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: a0bdb16889ee11c44b0783c2bc51a41c, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 30
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 0
    m_MaxSize: 50
    m_Alignment: 1
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 1
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "The final stage of conversion and the toughest of Aletheia\u2019s spawn. 
    Flesh Beetles possess a hide made straight from Aletheia herself and are equipped
    with a stinger used to pierce prey.  More often than not, flesh beetles are made
    up of reaper corpses and sometimes even previous humans who refused Aletheia\u2019s
    offer, their bodies melted and being combined to form a creature larger than
    any of the creatures that roam purgatory.  Despite being the most dangerous,
    they are not as trusted as the reapers due to their unpredictability caused by
    a loss of consciousness during the transition.  Flesh beetles can live forever
    as long as Aletheia remains living in the purgatorial realm.  Despite this, Aletheia
    will often take apart flesh beetles and make what is left part of her body."
