  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: a0bdb16889ee11c44b0783c2bc51a41c, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 30
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 0
    m_MaxSize: 50
    m_Alignment: 1
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 1
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: 'Aletheia: The old god that rules over the desolate realm of purgatory. 
    Often known as the goddess of truth, Aletheia has remained persistent in her
    eternal conquest to invade Heaven and Hell and eventually, transcend dimensions
    by invading the mortal realm.  Instead of promising false happiness, Aletheia
    chooses to break down the human souls who find themselves in purgatory by showing
    them all of their faults and trauma during their existence in the mortal realm. 
    After the spirit has been broken, Aletheia proposes a deal that if they can pass
    her 4 trials then she will grant eternal servitude.  Most accept this deal and
    become the roaming creatures of the purgatorial realm.  Those that refuse are
    melted and their flesh adds on to her increasing size.  '
